# QA First

## Before production telephony changes

If changing production telephony behavior or deploying to EC2:

1. **Run regression tests** — `npm run qa` (minimum) or `npm run qa:full` (protected files)
2. **Review HTML report** — `reports/qa-report-latest.html`
3. **Deploy only if tests pass** — see `docs/vsp/deployment/15-qa-regression.md`

## Protected telephony files

If modifying any protected component:

- `lib/inboundCallControl.js`
- `lib/telnyxCallControl.js`
- `lib/callControlSessionStore.js`
- `web/src/lib/webrtc-audio.ts`
- `web/src/lib/telnyx-softphone-session.ts`
- `web/src/app/(app)/softphone-v2/page.tsx`

**Run full telephony regression:**

```bash
npm run qa:full
```

Includes: Vitest suite + `validate:blind-transfer` + `validate:rapid-accept-stress` + `validate:extension-did`.

## Live call tests

Optional manual/live layer:

```bash
QA_LIVE_CALLS=true QA_LIVE_WEBRTC=true npm run test:telephony
QA_BROWSER_TESTS=true WEB_BASE=https://app.vspphone.com npm run test:browser
```

